[3]
Date: Wed 8 Sep 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Viet Nam News Agency (VNA), 7 Sep 2004 [edited]
<http://www.vnagency.com.vn/NewsA.aspLANGUAGE_ID=2&CATEGORY_ID=33&NEWS_ID=11689>


Malaysian boy hospitalized, over 1200 chickens destroyed
--------------------------------------------------------
A 10-year-old boy has been quarantined at a hospital, as a
precautionary measure, following the discovery of a new bird flu case
in Kampung Belian, in the east coast town of Tumpat. The new case was
confirmed as H5 bird flu infection by the Veterinary Research
Institute (VRI), in the northern town of Ipoh, last Sunday [5 Sep
2004], local media reported.

Kelantan Health Department Director Dr. Ahmad Razin Ahmad Maher said that the
boy, who lives with his family, was placed in a special ward at 7:30 last
night [6 Sep 2004] after coming down with fever.

The east coast state of Kelantan Veterinary Department, on Monday [6 Sep
2004] night, immediately launched a large-scale operation, culling over 1200
chickens and reared birds, to prevent the spread of H5 avian influenza, or
H5N1.

"So far, only the boy has the fever, but other members of the family,
and the villagers, show no signs of infection," he was quoted as
saying on Tuesday [7 Sep 2004].

Kelantan VSD Director Dr. Idris Kadir said that the operation to cull
poultry, within a 1km radius of the site of infection, began last night [6
Sep 2004] and involved 70 veterinary staff with help from 90 members of the
state health department.

